You may observe older user processes in ABAS.
This can be caused by network interruption.
The process keep running and blocks licence. Over time this causes reduced number of free licences,
and users get access refused.

This script can be run periodically from cron. It looks at the current user processes
extracts the age of them, and kills all those that exceed a defined age limit.

This intervention in mission critiical processes is properly documented via syslog.
